<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Antenna mainly dark brown except scape yellow, pedicel and first flagellomere brown; both ends of flagellomere with obvious expansion (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 26–28" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 26 - 28. Nephrotoma evittata Alexander, 1935. 26 Male habitus, lateral view 27 head and thorax, dorsal view 28 wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.973.46384.figures26-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/459926" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">26</figureCitation>
). Scutellum dark yellow, with brown middle stripe. Mediotergite yellow with brown to dark-yellow middle stripe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 26–28" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 26 - 28. Nephrotoma evittata Alexander, 1935. 26 Male habitus, lateral view 27 head and thorax, dorsal view 28 wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.973.46384.figures26-28" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/459926" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">27</figureCitation>
). Tergite 9 semicircular, depressed at middle, with a pair of sharp short protuberances at posterior margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 29–33" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 29 - 33. Nephrotoma evittata Alexander, 1935. 29 Hypopygium, lateral view 30 outer gonostylus, lateral external view 31 inner gonostylus, lateral external view 32 tergite 9, dorsal view 33 hypopygium, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (29, 32, 33); 0.1 mm (30, 31)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.973.46384.figures29-33" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/459927" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">32</figureCitation>
). Inner gonostylus with flat lower beak bearing bristles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 29–33" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 29 - 33. Nephrotoma evittata Alexander, 1935. 29 Hypopygium, lateral view 30 outer gonostylus, lateral external view 31 inner gonostylus, lateral external view 32 tergite 9, dorsal view 33 hypopygium, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (29, 32, 33); 0.1 mm (30, 31)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.973.46384.figures29-33" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/459927" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
