<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">China (Sichuan, Yunnan and Xizang).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
First record for Xizang. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="impigra" genus="N." lsidName="N. impigra subsp. impigra" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="subSpecies" species="impigra" subSpecies="impigra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">N. impigra impigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Alexander, 1935 from China (Hubei, Sichuan, Zhejiang, Fujian, Guizhou, Jiangxi), but the latter differs in the following characters: occipital marking distinct; scutellum dark brown. The hypopygium of this species is consistent with holotype, and we found that its occipital marking is variable. We think the difference between the veins is caused by the origin, which is also variable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
